<p></p>.<p>The medical term for vomiting blood (bloody vomit) is hematemesis.
Blood in vomit can be due to minor or major health problems.  It can be minimal or great in amount. <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/nausea_and_vomiting/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">Vomiting</a> blood should be evaluated by a health care professional.</p>.<p class="credits">REFERENCE:<br><br>Kasper, D.L., et al., eds. <i>Harrison's Principles of Internal Medicine, 19th Ed</i>. United States: McGraw-Hill Education, 2015.</p>